1
00:00:32,458 --> 00:00:34,166
( theme music playing )

2
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:43,125
♪ CAN'T YOU SEE
THAT I AM A PIONEER? ♪

3
00:00:43,208 --> 00:00:46,416
♪ UNLOCKING
THE GREATEST MYSTERIES ♪

4
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:51,416
♪ MY KEY IS A FEARLESS HEART
SO PURE AND STRONG ♪

5
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:54,583
♪ YOU CAN'T BE A HERO ♪

6
00:00:54,666 --> 00:00:57,500
♪ HIDING UNDERNEATH YOUR BED ♪

7
00:00:57,583 --> 00:01:00,416
♪ GOT TO LIVE THE LIFE ♪

8
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:03,458
♪ YOU CREATE INSIDE YOUR HEAD ♪

9
00:01:03,541 --> 00:01:06,500
♪ SO I OPEN THE WINDOW ♪

10
00:01:06,583 --> 00:01:09,500
♪ CAUGHT THE WIND ONE NIGHT ♪

11
00:01:09,583 --> 00:01:12,458
♪ NOW I SAIL WITH THE BIRDS ♪

12
00:01:12,541 --> 00:01:15,875
♪ IN THEIR FLIGHT ♪

13
00:01:15,958 --> 00:01:18,666
♪ SOME WILL SAY ♪

14
00:01:18,750 --> 00:01:21,083
♪ YOU'RE SAFER HERE ♪

15
00:01:21,166 --> 00:01:26,041
♪ NEVER MIND THAT,
BE A PIONEER ♪

16
00:01:28,041 --> 00:01:33,166
♪ CAN'T YOU SEE
THAT YOU ARE A PIONEER? ♪

17
00:01:33,250 --> 00:01:36,250
♪ NOT ONE
OF THE ENDLESS TALKERS ♪

18
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:38,333
♪ WHO TELL YOU
THE SAME OLD RULES ♪

19
00:01:38,416 --> 00:01:40,416
♪ YOU'VE HEARD BEFORE ♪

20
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:43,541
♪ WE WILL BE PIONEERS ♪

21
00:01:43,625 --> 00:01:45,416
♪ FOREVERMORE. ♪

22
00:02:03,125 --> 00:02:06,625
- ( birds singing )

23
00:02:08,458 --> 00:02:11,208
- HMM.
WELL WELL.

24
00:02:11,291 --> 00:02:13,500
HMM, THIS IS QUITE A MESS.

25
00:02:16,166 --> 00:02:18,875
- GEE, WHAT A DUMP. ARE WE
REALLY GOING TO STAY HERE?

26
00:02:18,958 --> 00:02:21,083
- HEY, YOU MADE THIS MESS!

27
00:02:21,166 --> 00:02:24,250
- OH MY!
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU CARED.

28
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:26,083
HOW SWEET.
- ( sighs )

29
00:02:26,166 --> 00:02:27,791
- WELCOME.

30
00:02:27,875 --> 00:02:30,500
IT'S A LONG TRIP.
THANKS FOR COMING ALL THE WAY.

31
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:33,166
- WELL, THANK YOU
FOR INVITING US BACK AGAIN.

32
00:02:33,250 --> 00:02:35,208
( laughs ) 

33
00:02:35,291 --> 00:02:37,000
- HERE YOU GO.
- HMM?

34
00:02:37,083 --> 00:02:39,833
MMM!

35
00:02:39,916 --> 00:02:42,833
- BOYS, YOU GET TO WORK
REPAIRING THE DAMAGE.

36
00:02:42,916 --> 00:02:46,291
GIRLS, YOU START ON CLEANING,
LAUNDRY AND COOKING.

37
00:02:46,375 --> 00:02:48,250
- ( all grumbling )

38
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:50,000
- BUT WE'RE TIRED.

39
00:02:50,083 --> 00:02:52,416
CAN'T WE REST
A LITTLE BIT FIRST?

40
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:54,250
- WHAT DID YOU SAY?
- HMM?  ME?

41
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:55,958
OH, NOTHING.

42
00:02:56,041 --> 00:02:58,583
- WE SHOULD PROBABLY
DO WHAT SHE SAYS.

43
00:02:58,666 --> 00:03:01,416
- THAT'S RIGHT.
COME ON, LET'S GO NOW.

44
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:03,833
- EXCUSE ME, MA'AM.
PARDON ME.

45
00:03:03,916 --> 00:03:06,833
WHAT'S MY ASSIGNMENT TO BE?
- YOU'RE NEW, AREN'T YOU?

46
00:03:06,916 --> 00:03:08,541
- YES I AM.

47
00:03:08,625 --> 00:03:10,875
HOW DO YOU DO?
MY NAME IS WASHU

48
00:03:10,958 --> 00:03:14,750
AND I AM AT YOUR SERVICE,
O GREAT RESPECTED ONE.

49
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:17,333
- WELL WELL,
FOR BEING SO YOUNG AND ALL,

50
00:03:17,416 --> 00:03:20,708
YOU ARE A GOOD POLITE GIRL
AND I LIKE THAT.

51
00:03:20,791 --> 00:03:23,875
NOW I'M NOT PLANNING ON MAKING
ANY CHILDREN DO ANY WORK,

52
00:03:23,958 --> 00:03:27,208
SO WHY DON'T YOU RUN ALONG
WITH SASAMI AND PLAY?

53
00:03:27,291 --> 00:03:28,666
- AHA!

54
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:29,791
YES, MA'AM.

55
00:03:29,875 --> 00:03:31,083
- HMM?

56
00:03:31,166 --> 00:03:32,875
- HUH?

57
00:03:32,958 --> 00:03:34,708
- HMM!

58
00:03:34,791 --> 00:03:36,916
- WASHU, YOU SLACKER!

59
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,291
OUCH!

60
00:03:38,375 --> 00:03:40,708
JUST WHAT THE--

61
00:03:40,791 --> 00:03:43,166
- QUIT WASTING MY TIME.

62
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:45,625
- ( grumbles )

63
00:03:48,083 --> 00:03:50,083
- ( laughs ) 

64
00:03:50,166 --> 00:03:52,125
- AH, NOBUYUKI.

65
00:03:52,208 --> 00:03:53,916
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE A PARTY OF EIGHT,

66
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,000
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE
WE'VE GOT ONE MORE GUEST.

67
00:03:56,083 --> 00:03:59,208
- HUH?  HMM?

68
00:03:59,291 --> 00:04:01,250
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

69
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:04,125
THERE ARE ONLY EIGHT OF US.

70
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:10,791
- THAT'S STRANGE.
I COULD SWEAR I SAW A YOUNG LADY

71
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:13,125
RESEMBLING ME AS A YOUNG WOMAN.

72
00:04:13,208 --> 00:04:15,333
- WELL, THERE'S NO ONE LIKE THAT
WITH US.

73
00:04:15,416 --> 00:04:18,625
NOT AT ALL.
- SHE'S STARTING TO SEE THINGS.

74
00:04:19,958 --> 00:04:21,708
WATCH OUT!
- OH!

75
00:04:21,791 --> 00:04:23,958
- I SAID GET TO WORK
AND I MEAN IT!

76
00:04:24,041 --> 00:04:25,666
- All: YES, MA'AM.

77
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:28,625
- SHALL WE GO?
- OKAY.

78
00:04:28,708 --> 00:04:30,416
HMMM.

79
00:04:31,708 --> 00:04:33,708
HEY, AYEKA.

80
00:04:33,791 --> 00:04:35,333
- HMM?

81
00:04:35,416 --> 00:04:37,791
- UH, NOTHING.

82
00:04:37,875 --> 00:04:38,958
NEVER MIND.

83
00:04:39,041 --> 00:04:41,583
- ALL RIGHT.

84
00:04:41,666 --> 00:04:43,500
- COME ON NOW, SASAMI.

85
00:04:43,583 --> 00:04:45,333
- OKAY.

86
00:05:00,208 --> 00:05:02,000
- THIS IS A MILFOIL.

87
00:05:02,083 --> 00:05:04,916
DID YOU KNOW THESE FLOWERS
ARE SUPPOSEDLY GROWN

88
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,125
FOR THEIR BEAUTY
AND MEDICINAL VALUES?

89
00:05:07,208 --> 00:05:09,166
BUT I WONDER WHAT THEY CURE.

90
00:05:10,375 --> 00:05:12,291
SASAMI?
- HUH?

91
00:05:12,375 --> 00:05:13,958
- COME OVER HERE, SASAMI.

92
00:05:14,041 --> 00:05:16,875
COME ON, IT'S A WONDERFUL VIEW.
IT REALLY IS.

93
00:05:21,208 --> 00:05:22,958
- WOW.

94
00:05:23,041 --> 00:05:24,583
( gasps )

95
00:05:24,666 --> 00:05:27,416
- ( yawning )

96
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:29,458
AH!  SASAMI?

97
00:05:29,541 --> 00:05:30,708
WHAT?

98
00:05:30,791 --> 00:05:34,166
- ( animals scurrying )

99
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:35,833
- WHERE'D SHE GO?

100
00:05:35,916 --> 00:05:38,875
OH WELL.
RYO-OHKI IS WITH HER

101
00:05:38,958 --> 00:05:41,083
SO SHE'LL BE FINE, I'M SURE.

102
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:43,250
- ( banging )

103
00:05:45,250 --> 00:05:47,666
- Nobuyuki: THIS MUST BE
WHAT SHE HAD IN MIND

104
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:49,833
WHEN SHE CALLED
AND INVITED US OVER.

105
00:05:49,916 --> 00:05:53,250
HMM, I WAS SO STUPID.

106
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:55,541
- Yosho: LET'S JUST SAY NAIVE.

107
00:05:55,625 --> 00:05:58,250
- WELL, YOU WERE EXCITED
ABOUT COMING HERE TOO.

108
00:05:58,333 --> 00:06:00,083
- DID YOU SAY SOMETHING?

109
00:06:00,166 --> 00:06:02,500
- UH, NO.
NOTHING NOTHING.

110
00:06:02,583 --> 00:06:05,541
( laughs ) 
OH!

111
00:06:05,625 --> 00:06:09,208
- MMM.
I TOLD YOU TO BE CAREFUL.

112
00:06:09,291 --> 00:06:11,375
OH!

113
00:06:11,458 --> 00:06:13,833
- ( both grunting )

114
00:06:13,916 --> 00:06:15,375
- BONEHEADS.

115
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:17,875
- HEY, TENCHI, LOOK.
- HMM?

116
00:06:17,958 --> 00:06:20,958
- OH!
- NOW WHO'S A BONEHEAD?

117
00:06:21,041 --> 00:06:22,583
- AHH!

118
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:33,666
- HMM.  YOU'RE A BIG HELP.

119
00:06:33,750 --> 00:06:35,458
WITH THE WAY
YOU'RE PEELING THEM,

120
00:06:35,541 --> 00:06:37,333
WE WON'T HAVE ANYTHING
LEFT TO EAT.

121
00:06:37,416 --> 00:06:39,083
- IS THAT RIGHT?

122
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:40,958
WELL, WITH HOW SLOWLY
YOU'RE PEELING THEM,

123
00:06:41,041 --> 00:06:43,208
WE'RE NEVER GONNA FINISH,
MADAM SLOWPOKE.

124
00:06:43,291 --> 00:06:44,916
- MM-HMM!

125
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:48,250
WELL, AT LEAST I HAVE A TALENT
FOR NOT WASTING FOOD.

126
00:06:48,333 --> 00:06:50,291
- WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?
- THE TRUTH!

127
00:06:50,375 --> 00:06:51,833
- ( both grumble )

128
00:06:51,916 --> 00:06:53,625
- SETTLE DOWN, BOTH OF YOU.

129
00:06:53,708 --> 00:06:56,125
I MEAN, LET'S NOT ARGUE
OVER NOTHING, OKAY?

130
00:06:56,208 --> 00:06:59,833
I MEAN, AT LEAST WAIT TILL
IT'S SOMETHING TO ARGUE ABOUT.

131
00:06:59,916 --> 00:07:01,958
- Both: MMM.

132
00:07:03,791 --> 00:07:05,916
EH.  OOH!

133
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:09,541
- WHAT?

134
00:07:11,625 --> 00:07:13,416
HMM!

135
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:15,958
- HEY, I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

136
00:07:16,041 --> 00:07:17,958
- ( sighs )

137
00:07:19,458 --> 00:07:21,875
- IT WASN'T ME, I TELL YOU.

138
00:07:21,958 --> 00:07:25,625
I REALLY DIDN'T DO ANYTHING
AND YOU'D BETTER BELIEVE ME.

139
00:07:27,416 --> 00:07:29,458
SASAMI, WAS IT YOU?

140
00:07:29,541 --> 00:07:32,458
- ( meows ) 
- OH, AYEKA.

141
00:07:32,541 --> 00:07:34,083
- HMM?

142
00:07:34,166 --> 00:07:37,708
DID YOU SEE SOMEONE ELSE HERE
JUST NOW?

143
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:39,875
- NO, AYEKA, I DIDN'T.

144
00:07:39,958 --> 00:07:42,708
- ( meows ) 
- I THOUGHT I SAW SOMEONE.

145
00:07:42,791 --> 00:07:45,208
- AYEKA, I NEED TO TELL YOU--
- Ryoko: HEY, AYEKA!

146
00:07:45,291 --> 00:07:48,041
WHAT WAS IT?
- OH, NOTHING!

147
00:07:48,125 --> 00:07:51,333
UH, SASAMI, YOU WERE SAYING?

148
00:07:51,416 --> 00:07:53,458
- UH, NOTHING REALLY.

149
00:07:55,666 --> 00:07:57,708
- HMM?  MMM.

150
00:07:59,291 --> 00:08:00,416
- ( hammering )

151
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:01,916
- PLEASE HOLD IT TIGHT,
GRANDPA.

152
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,750
- I KNOW.  HURRY UP.

153
00:08:08,208 --> 00:08:09,083
- HMM?

154
00:08:10,833 --> 00:08:13,541
AHHH.

155
00:08:13,625 --> 00:08:16,083
DID-- DID YOU--
DID YOU SEE THAT?

156
00:08:16,166 --> 00:08:18,458
- HMM.

157
00:08:21,625 --> 00:08:24,166
- ( men groaning )

158
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:27,458
- SHH!  I'M TELLING YOU
WHAT WE SAW.

159
00:08:27,541 --> 00:08:30,833
WE SAW A VAGUE GHOSTLIKE FIGURE.

160
00:08:30,916 --> 00:08:35,083
- OKAY, YOU-- YOU GUYS ARE JUST
TRYING TO SCARE ME NOW, RIGHT?

161
00:08:35,166 --> 00:08:37,083
- NO, WE ACTUALLY SAW IT.

162
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:39,291
- MMM.

163
00:08:39,375 --> 00:08:41,583
- YOU SAW IT?
- Ayeka: YES.

164
00:08:41,666 --> 00:08:42,958
- AHH!

165
00:08:43,041 --> 00:08:45,250
- COME TO THINK OF IT,
DAD AND GRANDPA

166
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:47,541
SAID THEY SAW SOMETHING--
SOMETHING SIMILAR.

167
00:08:47,625 --> 00:08:50,250
- Mihoshi: STOP IT, PLEASE.
I CAN'T STAND IT.

168
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:53,500
I CAN'T STAND IT.

169
00:08:53,583 --> 00:08:55,500
- WHAT ARE YOU AFRAID OF,
TENCHI?

170
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:57,541
- HEY, DO I LOOK AFRAID?!

171
00:08:57,625 --> 00:08:59,041
- AHH!

172
00:08:59,125 --> 00:09:01,541
- OH! GRANDPA!

173
00:09:01,625 --> 00:09:02,791
- LISTEN.

174
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:05,541
I'LL TELL YOU THE STORY.

175
00:09:05,625 --> 00:09:06,875
WHEN I WAS A YOUNG MAN,

176
00:09:06,958 --> 00:09:08,750
THE PERSON WHO LIVED
HERE TOLD IT TO ME.

177
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:11,500
IT BEGINS OVER 600 YEARS AGO.

178
00:09:11,583 --> 00:09:15,541
THERE WAS A HOUSE ON A MOUNTAIN
FAR AWAY FROM CIVILIZATION.

179
00:09:15,625 --> 00:09:17,541
IN IT, THERE LIVED A COUPLE.

180
00:09:17,625 --> 00:09:20,000
PEOPLE RESPECTED AND
ADMIRED THEIR RELATIONSHIP

181
00:09:20,083 --> 00:09:22,458
BECAUSE THEY WERE
SO MUCH IN LOVE.

182
00:09:22,541 --> 00:09:25,250
HOWEVER, THE WIFE
HAD BEEN SICKLY SINCE CHILDHOOD

183
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:27,791
AND HAD BECOME BEDRIDDEN
FOR QUITE SOME TIME.

184
00:09:27,875 --> 00:09:30,416
IT IS SAID
SHE PROBABLY KNEW

185
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:32,541
THAT HER TIME
WAS RUNNING SHORT.

186
00:09:32,625 --> 00:09:34,958
THEY DID THEIR BEST
TRYING TO CARE FOR EACH OTHER

187
00:09:35,041 --> 00:09:37,375
AND LIVE THEIR LIVES
TO THE FULLEST

188
00:09:37,458 --> 00:09:41,833
AND TO TREASURE
THEIR REMAINING TIME TOGETHER.

189
00:09:41,916 --> 00:09:43,375
ONE STORMY NIGHT,

190
00:09:43,458 --> 00:09:45,791
THEY HEARD A VOICE
THROUGH THE HOWLING WIND.

191
00:09:45,875 --> 00:09:49,916
IT WASN'T THEIR IMAGINATION.
THE VOICE WAS REAL.

192
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,958
THOUGH THEY WERE SCARED,
THEY WERE COMPELLED TO LISTEN.

193
00:09:53,041 --> 00:09:55,750
AND THIS IS WHAT
THE VOICE SAID TO THEM--

194
00:09:55,833 --> 00:09:58,166
"HEAD TO THE WEST.

195
00:09:58,250 --> 00:10:01,208
GO OVER THREE MOUNTAINS
AND YOU'LL FIND AN HERB

196
00:10:01,291 --> 00:10:04,041
THAT CAN CURE
ANY KIND OF SICKNESS."

197
00:10:04,125 --> 00:10:08,708
THUS THE WIND SPOKE
AND THEN FELL SILENT.

198
00:10:08,791 --> 00:10:10,750
THE HUSBAND
BELIEVED THE WIND'S WORDS

199
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:12,958
AND DECIDED TO GO SEARCH
FOR THE HERB.

200
00:10:13,041 --> 00:10:16,166
SHE BEGGED HIM TO REMAIN
AND NOT LEAVE HER ALONE,

201
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:18,958
BUT HE LEFT
AND SET OUT FOR THE WEST.

202
00:10:19,041 --> 00:10:20,416
- HUH?

203
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:22,541
MMM!
- OW!

204
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:28,291
- FOR SIX MONTHS,
SHE WAITED FOR HIS RETURN,

205
00:10:28,375 --> 00:10:31,333
HOLDING ON AGAINST DEATH
WITH ALL HER STRENGTH.

206
00:10:31,416 --> 00:10:33,625
BUT HE DIDN'T RETURN.

207
00:10:33,708 --> 00:10:37,708
SHE SPOKE TO HERSELF, SAYING,
"I WISH THAT I WERE HEALTHY.

208
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:40,208
THEN I WOULD BE ABLE
TO LOOK FOR HIM."

209
00:10:40,291 --> 00:10:43,666
BUT, ALAS,
HER HOPES WERE IN VAIN.

210
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:46,458
AND ONE DAY, ALL ALONE,

211
00:10:46,541 --> 00:10:49,375
SHE PASSED AWAY.

212
00:10:49,458 --> 00:10:52,583
AFTER THAT DAY
AROUND THIS PLACE,

213
00:10:52,666 --> 00:10:55,041
PEOPLE BEGAN TO SEE AN IMAGE
OF A WOMAN.

214
00:10:55,125 --> 00:10:57,708
THEY CALL HER THE WHITE GHOST.

215
00:10:57,791 --> 00:11:00,041
SO YOU'D BETTER
WATCH OUT, TENCHI.

216
00:11:00,125 --> 00:11:01,541
- HMM?

217
00:11:01,625 --> 00:11:05,000
- HER SPIRIT WANDERS AIMLESSLY,
SEARCHING FOR HER BELOVED,

218
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:09,541
CONSTANTLY SEARCHING.
SHE MAY EVEN COME FOR YOU.

219
00:11:11,166 --> 00:11:12,833
- HEY!
- AHH!

220
00:11:12,916 --> 00:11:14,416
- ( all shouting )

221
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:16,541
- HAVEN'T YOU RESTED
LONG ENOUGH?

222
00:11:16,625 --> 00:11:18,583
GET BACK TO WORK!

223
00:11:20,458 --> 00:11:23,125
- All: OH YES, MA'AM!
- OH!

224
00:11:23,208 --> 00:11:24,833
- KIDS TODAY!

225
00:11:24,916 --> 00:11:28,083
EH, THAT GOES FOR YOU TOO,
I HOPE YOU KNOW.

226
00:11:28,166 --> 00:11:31,291
- BUT-- BUT I--
THE WHITE GHOST IS--

227
00:11:31,375 --> 00:11:34,208
- NOT THE WHITE GHOST!

228
00:11:35,875 --> 00:11:38,041
THAT OLD STORY OF YOURS AGAIN?

229
00:11:38,125 --> 00:11:39,541
- YOU-- YOUR STORY?

230
00:11:39,625 --> 00:11:41,708
THEN YOU MADE IT ALL UP?

231
00:11:41,791 --> 00:11:43,833
- ( laughs ) 

232
00:11:43,916 --> 00:11:46,083
YUP.
NOT MAD, ARE YOU?

233
00:11:46,166 --> 00:11:48,291
- Innkeeper: CUT IT OUT!
- ( laughs ) 

234
00:11:48,375 --> 00:11:49,333
OH!

235
00:11:49,416 --> 00:11:51,250
GO RIG THE LIGHTS
OR SOMETHING.

236
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:56,833
- WHEN WILL THEY EVER GROW UP?

237
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:06,416
WHY AM I THE ONE
WHO HAS TO FIX THIS?

238
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:09,375
DAD AND GRANDPA ARE ALWAYS
SITTING AROUND DOING NOTHING.

239
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:15,458
HUH?

240
